# IP Reputation Blocklist for WordPress Hardening Plugin
# -------------------------------------------------------
# Add IP addresses and/or CIDR ranges to block, one entry per line.
# IPv4 and IPv6 are both supported. CIDR notation is supported (e.g. 203.0.113.0/24).
# Lines starting with # are comments and are ignored by ModSecurity.
#
# Enable blocking with:
#   SecAction "id:9522053,phase:1,nolog,pass,t:none,setvar:'tx.wphard.ip_reputation_enabled=1'"
# (see plugins/wordpress-hardening-config.conf for configuration details)
#
# Threat intelligence sources to consider:
#   - Emerging Threats: https://rules.emergingthreats.net/fwrules/
#   - Spamhaus DROP: https://www.spamhaus.org/drop/drop.txt
#   - Firehol Level 1: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/firehol/blocklist-ipsets/master/firehol_level1.netset
#
# RFC 5737 documentation/test addresses (192.0.2.0/24, 198.51.100.0/24, 203.0.113.0/24)
# are listed below for CI test verification. These ranges are reserved for documentation
# purposes and are never used on the public internet; you may safely remove them in production.

192.0.2.0/24
